# [Bitwise Operators](https://www.hackerrank.com/challenges/bitwise-operators-in-c/problem?isFullScreen=true)
## Easy
<div class="challenge-body-html"><div class="challenge_problem_statement"><div class="msB challenge_problem_statement_body"><div class="hackdown-content"><svg style="display: none;"><defs id="MathJax_SVG_glyphs"></defs></svg><p>In this challenge, you will use logical bitwise operators.  All data is stored in its binary representation.  The logical operators, and C language, use <span style="font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;" class="MathJax_SVG" id="MathJax-Element-1-Frame"><svg xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="1.162ex" height="2.176ex" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex;" viewBox="0 -791.3 500.5 936.9" role="img" focusable="false"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)"><path stroke-width="1" d="M213 578L200 573Q186 568 160 563T102 556H83V602H102Q149 604 189 617T245 641T273 663Q275 666 285 666Q294 666 302 660V361L303 61Q310 54 315 52T339 48T401 46H427V0H416Q395 3 257 3Q121 3 100 0H88V46H114Q136 46 152 46T177 47T193 50T201 52T207 57T213 61V578Z"></path></g></svg></span> to represent true and <span style="font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;" class="MathJax_SVG" id="MathJax-Element-2-Frame"><svg xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="1.162ex" height="2.176ex" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex;" viewBox="0 -791.3 500.5 936.9" role="img" focusable="false"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)"><path stroke-width="1" d="M96 585Q152 666 249 666Q297 666 345 640T423 548Q460 465 460 320Q460 165 417 83Q397 41 362 16T301 -15T250 -22Q224 -22 198 -16T137 16T82 83Q39 165 39 320Q39 494 96 585ZM321 597Q291 629 250 629Q208 629 178 597Q153 571 145 525T137 333Q137 175 145 125T181 46Q209 16 250 16Q290 16 318 46Q347 76 354 130T362 333Q362 478 354 524T321 597Z"></path></g></svg></span> to represent false. The logical operators compare bits in two numbers and return true or false, <span style="font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;" class="MathJax_SVG" id="MathJax-Element-3-Frame"><svg xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="1.162ex" height="2.176ex" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex;" viewBox="0 -791.3 500.5 936.9" role="img" focusable="false"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)"><path stroke-width="1" d="M96 585Q152 666 249 666Q297 666 345 640T423 548Q460 465 460 320Q460 165 417 83Q397 41 362 16T301 -15T250 -22Q224 -22 198 -16T137 16T82 83Q39 165 39 320Q39 494 96 585ZM321 597Q291 629 250 629Q208 629 178 597Q153 571 145 525T137 333Q137 175 145 125T181 46Q209 16 250 16Q290 16 318 46Q347 76 354 130T362 333Q362 478 354 524T321 597Z"></path></g></svg></span> or <span style="font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;" class="MathJax_SVG" id="MathJax-Element-4-Frame"><svg xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="1.162ex" height="2.176ex" style="vertical-align: -0.338ex;" viewBox="0 -791.3 500.5 936.9" role="img" focusable="false"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)"><path stroke-width="1" d="M213 578L200 573Q186 568 160 563T102 556H83V602H102Q149 604 189 617T245 641T273 663Q275 666 285 666Q294 666 302 660V361L303 61Q310 54 315 52T339 48T401 46H427V0H416Q395 3 257 3Q121 3 100 0H88V46H114Q136 46 152 46T177 47T193 50T201 52T207 57T213 61V578Z"></path></g></svg></span>, for each bit compared.  </p>

<ul>
<li><p><code>Bitwise AND operator &amp;</code>  The output of bitwise AND is <em>1</em> if the corresponding bits of two operands is <em>1</em>. If either bit of an operand is <em>0</em>, the result of corresponding bit is evaluated to <em>0</em>. It is denoted by &amp;.</p></li>
<li><p><code>Bitwise OR operator |</code>  The output of bitwise OR is <em>1</em> if at least one corresponding bit of two operands is <em>1</em>. It is denoted by |.</p></li>
<li><p><code>Bitwise XOR (exclusive OR) operator ^</code>  The result of bitwise XOR operator is <em>1</em> if the corresponding bits of two operands are opposite. It is denoted by <span style="font-size: 100%; display: inline-block;" class="MathJax_SVG" id="MathJax-Element-5-Frame"><svg xmlns:xlink="http://www.w3.org/1999/xlink" width="1.808ex" height="2.176ex" style="vertical-align: -0.505ex;" viewBox="0 -719.6 778.5 936.9" role="img" focusable="false"><g stroke="currentColor" fill="currentColor" stroke-width="0" transform="matrix(1 0 0 -1 0 0)"><path stroke-width="1" d="M56 250Q56 394 156 488T384 583Q530 583 626 485T722 250Q722 110 625 14T390 -83Q249 -83 153 14T56 250ZM364 542Q308 539 251 509T148 418T96 278V270H369V542H364ZM681 278Q675 338 650 386T592 462T522 509T458 535T412 542H409V270H681V278ZM96 222Q104 150 139 95T219 12T302 -29T366 -42H369V230H96V222ZM681 222V230H409V-42H412Q429 -42 456 -36T521 -10T590 37T649 113T681 222Z"></path></g></svg></span>.</p></li>
</ul>

<p>For example, for integers 3 and 5,</p>

<div class="highlight"><pre><span></span><span class="mi">3</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mo">00000011</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">In</span> <span class="n">Binary</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="mi">5</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mo">00000101</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">In</span> <span class="n">Binary</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">AND</span> <span class="n">operation</span>        <span class="n">OR</span> <span class="n">operation</span>        <span class="n">XOR</span> <span class="n">operation</span>
  <span class="mo">00000011</span>             <span class="mo">00000011</span>            <span class="mo">00000011</span>
<span class="o">&amp;</span> <span class="mo">00000101</span>           <span class="o">|</span> <span class="mo">00000101</span>          <span class="o">^</span> <span class="mo">00000101</span>
  <span class="n">________</span>             <span class="n">________</span>            <span class="n">________</span>
  <span class="mo">00000001</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">1</span>        <span class="mo">00000111</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">7</span>       <span class="mo">00000110</span>  <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">6</span>
</pre></div>

<p><strong>Function Description</strong>  </p>

<p>Complete the <em>calculate_the_maximum</em> function in the editor below.  </p>

<p><em>calculate_the_maximum</em> has the following parameters:  </p>

<ul>
<li><em>int n:</em> the highest number to consider  </li>
<li><em>int k:</em> the result of a comparison must be lower than this number to be considered  </li>
</ul>

<p><strong>Prints</strong>  </p>
